CHSC5816 - I2C Touch Driver
devices

Detailed Description

Purpose: This module provides a hardware abstraction layer for the CHSC5816 capacitive touch sensor, enabling reliable touch detection, event processing, and power-efficient operation for embedded applications requiring touch input capabilities. The driver supports multiple touch channels, customizable configuration, and features like gesture recognition and state tracking for optimal user interface performance and system integration.

Key Features

  1. Multi-channel Touch: Supports multiple touch inputs.
  2. Gesture Recognition: Detects gestures such as swipe and tap.
  3. State Management: Tracks touch state and changes.
  4. Power Efficiency: Low-power operation and sleep modes.
  5. Customizable Configuration: Flexible sensor and interrupt settings.

Functionality

  • Initialize CHSC5816 device
  • Configure touch channels and sensitivity
  • Track and update touch state
  • Support for gesture and event management

Usage

  1. Initialize the device with am_devices_chsc5816_init()
  2. Periodically call am_devices_chsc5816_poll() to process touch events
  3. Use am_devices_chsc5816_get_event() to retrieve touch or gesture events

Configuration

  • Configure touch channels and sensitivity
  • Set up interrupt and power management options
